The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Calcutta, July 21: Municipalities will fine an offender up to Rs 500 for littering roads and drains with plastic items. 

 The minimum fine would be Rs 100, muni-cipal affairs minister Asok Bhattacharya said in the Assembly.

 Calcutta: Land and land reforms minister Abdur Rezzak Mollah said on Friday the government would conduct a survey of agricultural land, crop pattern and use of 3.47 crore plots across the state. The findings would help frame the governments policy with regard to agriculture, urbanisation and industrialisation.

 Calcutta: The head of the oversight committee, assigned to draw a road map for the introduction of 27 per cent reservation for OBC students in higher academic institutions, said its recommendations will also protect the interests of general students. The road map has to ensure that the interests of the general-category students are not jeopardised. It must also protect the brand equity of the institutions, said Veerappa Moliy.

 Calcutta: The circular railway service between Dum Dum Cantonment and the airport will be flagged off on July 29. The 3.8-km stretch in which 2.8 km is elevated has two stations ? Jessore Road and Airport.




